  , issueBody =
      Just
        "If a large number of documents are being inserted via soft durability, and the server receives a shutdown signal, RethinkDB will attempt to flush all dirty data absorbed by RAM to disk.\r\n\r\nThe user receives no indication that this is happening, beyond using tools like `iostat` or `iotop` to observe a high volume of disk writes.\r\n\r\nIt would be useful to add a message stating \"Flushing data to disk\" and a progress bar indicating how many docs / blocks remain to be flushed."
